responded: Now I understand the issue better. The problem is that when `xmlXIncludeProcessFlags` is called, it can modify the document structure and free nodes that are still referenced by PHP DOM objects. When these objects are later freed during shutdown, they try to access already freed memory.

The solution is to invalidate the node list cache BEFORE calling `xmlXIncludeProcessFlags`, not after. This will ensure that any cached references to nodes that might be freed during XInclude processing are invalidated.

